From: "Kirill A. Shutemov" <kirill.shutemov@linux.intel.com>
Date: Thu, 28 Dec 2023 17:47:03 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] mm, treewide: introduce NR_PAGE_ORDERS
References: bsc#1218260
Patch-mainline: 6.6.30
Git-commit: fd37721803c6e73619108f76ad2e12a9aa5fafaf

[ Upstream commit fd37721803c6e73619108f76ad2e12a9aa5fafaf ]

NR_PAGE_ORDERS defines the number of page orders supported by the page
allocator, ranging from 0 to MAX_ORDER, MAX_ORDER + 1 in total.

NR_PAGE_ORDERS assists in defining arrays of page orders and allows for
more natural iteration over them.

